Recipe⬇️

250 g Bakescape’s whole wheat flour
15 g sugar
1/2 tsp salt
7 g yeast
15 g butter

Water as per requirement

Mix everything together and form an elastic dough by kneading it for 10-15 mins. You can take 2 min in break in between. This way the dough can rest and form stronger gluten strands. If the dough passes the window pane test, roll it properly and let it sit in a greased bowl. Oil the dough too with a pastry brush. Cover it and let it sit for 1 hour or so until it doubles in size. Then deflate it after proofing and shape it in a rectangular form. Keep it in a greased tin and bake it at 180c for 40-45 minutes. And there you go, you homemade whole wheat bread is ready!
